{"type":"message","id":"237bedd9","parentId":"f91f0118","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:05:41.140Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_twqbek4jaf8v_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 6133\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=117\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] a\r\n[mutation proposed] a\r\n[master e9e9ad1] pulse: 2026-03-24 150514\n 5 files changed, 187 insertions(+), 69 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 150514.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 150514.mutation\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 150514 - The CFI compression synthesis identified that constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1.0) need to be distinguished from research trajectory tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5). The hybrid formula score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120) needs empirical validation against existing pulse data.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"quiet-meadow","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 6133\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=117\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] a\r\n[mutation proposed] a\r\n[master e9e9ad1] pulse: 2026-03-24 150514\n 5 files changed, 187 insertions(+), 69 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 150514.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 150514.mutation\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 150514 - The CFI compression synthesis identified that constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1.0) need to be distinguished from research trajectory tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5). The hybrid formula score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120) needs empirical validation against existing pulse data.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774379141139}}
{"type":"message","id":"bce8b75d","parentId":"237bedd9","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:05:41.144Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_twqbek4jaf8v_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 150414\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/cfi_hybrid_experiment.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best single action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 (Architecture cross-analysis) are complete\r\n2. Gap-Decay synthesis is complete\r\n3. LLM-Augmented pulse is complete\r\n4. CFI Compression Experiment is complete with key findings\r\n\r\nThe next pending action is clearly:\r\n- **Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)** - Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nThe key insight is that the three-dimensional filter should be: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\nAnd the new scoring formula is: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nTo run this experiment, I need to:\r\n1. Have access to the pulse data\r\n2. Implement the new scoring formula\r\n3. Run the comparison\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist. The key research file is `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md`. I should create a new experiment file that implements the hybrid scoring approach and runs it on the pulses.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the pattern of previous pulses, I should create a new research document that:\r\n1. Documents the new scoring formula\r\n2. Implements the experiment\r\n3. Runs it on the 200 pulses\r\n\r\nLet me check what data files are available. The pulses are in `pulse_*.md` format. I need to compute CFI and frequency for each token, then apply the hybrid scoring.\r\n\r\nFor this pulse, I'll create the experiment script/results that tests the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring. This advances the pending goal directly.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe pending priority is the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C). The key insight from the CFI compression synthesis is that binary thresholds fail on \"constant format\" tokens (freq=160, CFI=1) which are metaprogramming artifacts. The hybrid formula score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) should distinguish these from true research tokens.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the hybrid scoring experiment document with token analysis comparing binary thresholds vs the new continuous scoring formula. This will test if the hybrid approach correctly scores constant-format tokens low while research tokens high.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment (Strategy C)\r\n**Created:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Status:** IN PROGRESS\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nThe hybrid formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` will:\r\n- Penalize constant-format tokens (freq≈160, CFI≈1) → score ≈ 1.0 (maxed, clearly artifact)\r\n- Boost research trajectory tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5) → score proportional to both signals\r\n- Distinguish \"for next instantiation\" (freq=160, CFI=1.00) from \"Phase 1\" (freq=136, CFI=0.96)\r\n\r\n## Scoring Function\r\n```python\r\ndef hybrid_score(cfi: float, freq: int) -> float:\r\n    \"\"\"CFI × normalized frequency, capped at 1.0\"\"\"\r\n    return cfi * min(1.0, freq / 120.0)\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Token Score Examples\r\n\r\n| Token | CFI | Freq | Binary (CFI≥0.5) | Hybrid Score | Classification |\r\n|-------|-----|------|------------------|-------------|----------------|\r\n| \"for next instantiation\" | 1.00 | 160 | ✓ (artifact) | 1.00 | constant-format |\r\n| \"pulse\" | 1.00 | 160 | ✓ (artifact) | 1.00 | constant-format |\r\n| \"completed at:\" | 1.00 | 160 | ✓ (artifact) | 1.00 | constant-format |\r\n| \"Phase 1\" | 0.96 | 136 | ✓ (valid) | 1.09→1.00 | research trajectory |\r\n| \"Phase 2\" | 0.85 | 45 | ✓ (valid) | 0.32 | research trajectory |\r\n| \"architecture\" | 0.72 | 89 | ✓ (valid) | 0.53 | research trajectory |\r\n| \"CFI\" | 0.68 | 72 | ✓ (valid) | 0.41 | research trajectory |\r\n| \"gap\" | 0.55 | 38 | ✓ (valid) | 0.17 | research trajectory |\r\n\r\n## Expected Outcomes\r\n- Binary threshold (CFI≥0.5) captures ALL tokens above, including constant-format artifacts\r\n- Hybrid scoring creates a **gradient** rather than binary pass/fail\r\n- High-freq, high-CFI tokens get max score (1.0) → identifies them as \"constant\"\r\n- Mid-freq, high-CFI tokens get proportional scores → true research signal\r\n\r\n## Next Step\r\nRun scoring on all 200 pulses, rank tokens by hybrid_score, validate against manual classification of 50 tokens.\r\n`\r\nfile: research/HYBRID_CFI_FREQ_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n`\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:04:35\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774379141140}}
